faq.question: What is a ghostwriter?
faq.reply: A ghostwriter is someone who gets paid to create the content for a book or e-book, but they don’t get the credit for being the author of the finished work. The person who will officially appear as the ‘author’ usually hires a freelance ghostwriter to produce the necessary content for an agreed fee. It’s assumed that there will be no acclaim for the ghostwriter’s contribution as all the credit goes to the person who hired them.
